{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"chatcmpl-tool-8f9135fc772953e6","type":"tool_result","content":"999\t\n1000\t0.754\n1001\t0.747\n1002\t0.796\n1003\t0.756\n1004\t0.794\n1005\t0.761\n1006\t\n1007\t0.716\n1008\t0.750\n1009\t0.709\n1010\t0.712\n1011\t0.750\n1012\t0.716\n1013\t\n1014\t0.788\n1015\t0.751\n1016\t0.751\n1017\t0.779\n1018\t0.774\n1019\t0.770\n1020\t\n1021\tFig. 4: Qualitative comparison of StoryTeller, AutoAD-Zero [38], and professional\n1022\treference AD. (GT).\n1023\t\n1024\tscenes. By maintaining an identity graph and structured narrative memory, the\n1025\tsystem generates coherent descriptions without task-specific training or curated\n1026\tmovie resources; public movie metadata can suggest context, but only videosupported facts enter memory. We also introduced StoryAD-QA, a benchmark\n1027\tfor evaluating whether generated AD supports narrative understanding. Experiments show that narrative-aware modeling improves contextual grounding and\n1028\tstory comprehension in long-form video description.\n1029\t\n1030\tAcknowledgments\n1031\tThis work was supported by startup funds provided by Dartmouth College. The\n1032\tauthors also acknowledge support from the National Science Foundation under\n1033\tCAREER Award No. 2541968.\n1034\t\n1035\t\f16\n1036\t\n1037\tS. H. Hahm et al.\n1038\t\n1039\tReferences\n1040\t1. Anderson, P., Fernando, B., Johnson, M., Gould, S.: Spice: Semantic propositional\n1041\timage caption evaluation. In: European Conference on Computer Vision (ECCV).\n1042\tSpringer (2016)\n1043\t2. Cheng, Z., Leng, S., Zhang, H., Xin, Y., Li, X., Chen, G., Zhu, Y., Zhang, W.,\n1044\tLuo, Z., Zhao, D., Bing, L.: Videollama 2: Advancing spatial-temporal modeling\n1045\tand audio understanding in video-llms (2024)\n1046\t3. Deng, J., Guo, J., Xue, N., Zafeiriou, S.: Arcface: Additive angular margin loss for\n1047\tdeep face recognition. In: Proceedings of the IEEE/CVF Conference on Computer\n1048\tVision and Patt