{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"chatcmpl-tool-8498fae6c50dd07b","type":"tool_result","content":"# Fish Audio S2 Technical Report\narXiv: 2603.08823\nAuthors: Shijia Liao, Yuxuan Wang, Songting Liu, Yifan Cheng, Ruoyi Zhang, Tianyu Li, Shidong Li, Yisheng Zheng, Xingwei Liu, Qingzheng Wang, Zhizhuo Zhou, Jiahua Liu, Xin Chen, Dawei Han\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A Dual-AR architecture that decouples temporal semantic modeling from depth-wise acoustic generation for efficient high-fidelity speech synthesis.\n  2. A dual-purpose data pipeline where speech quality and rich-transcription ASR models serve as both pre-training data filters and RL reward signals to eliminate distribution shift.\n  3. An RL-based post-training method using GRPO with multi-dimensional rewards to jointly optimize semantic accuracy, acoustic quality, and speaker similarity.\n  4. Native support for multi-speaker, multi-turn dialogue generation and stable long-form coherent audio synthesis.\n  5. Enhanced zero-shot instruction-following capabilities enabling fine-grained control over speech generation via natural language descriptions and inline vocal tags.\n  6. A production-ready SGLang-based inference engine achieving an RTF of 0.195 and a time-to-first-audio below 100 ms.\n  7. The introduction of the Fish Audio Instruction Benchmark to systematically evaluate fine-grained inline tag-following performance in TTS models.\n  8. The open-source release of the model weights, fine-tuning code, and inference engine to facilitate future TTS research.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-RL优化, TTS/控制-指令合成, TTS/功能-多说话人\n===\n# MOVA: Towards Scalable and Synchronized Video-Audio Generation\narXiv: 2602.08794\nAuthors: \nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We develop MOVA, a synchronized video-audio generation model with an asymmetric dual-tower architecture that leverages pre-trained video and audio generation models.\n  2. We design a fine-grained audio-video captioning pipeline to produce high-quality bimodal training data at scale.\n  3. By scaling video-audio training, we achieve continuous improvements in synchronization performance across both modalities.\n\nTags: related-work, we develop, we design, by scaling","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"206fc7a5-df8a-4bee-9d63-61742ae2bbd5","uuid":"5c7abe2d-4c49-4035-9fc3-d3e602534c6b","timestamp":"2026-07-14T11:44:23.261Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# Fish Audio S2 Technical Report\narXiv: 2603.08823\nAuthors: Shijia Liao, Yuxuan Wang, Songting Liu, Yifan Cheng, Ruoyi Zhang, Tianyu Li, Shidong Li, Yisheng Zheng, Xingwei Liu, Qingzheng Wang, Zhizhuo Zhou, Jiahua Liu, Xin Chen, Dawei Han\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A Dual-AR architecture that decouples temporal semantic modeling from depth-wise acoustic generation for efficient high-fidelity speech synthesis.\n  2. A dual-purpose data pipeline where speech quality and rich-transcription ASR models serve as both pre-training data filters and RL reward signals to eliminate distribution shift.\n  3. An RL-based post-training method using GRPO with multi-dimensional rewards to jointly optimize semantic accuracy, acoustic quality, and speaker similarity.\n  4. Native support for multi-speaker, multi-turn dialogue generation and stable long-form coherent audio synthesis.\n  5. Enhanced zero-shot instruction-following capabilities enabling fine-grained control over speech generation via natural language descriptions and inline vocal tags.\n  6. A production-ready SGLang-based inference engine achieving an RTF of 0.195 and a time-to-first-audio below 100 ms.\n  7. The introduction of the Fish Audio Instruction Benchmark to systematically evaluate fine-grained inline tag-following performance in TTS models.\n  8. The open-source release of the model weights, fine-tuning code, and inference engine to facilitate future TTS research.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-RL优化, TTS/控制-指令合成, TTS/功能-多说话人\n===\n# MOVA: Towards Scalable and Synchronized Video-Audio Generation\narXiv: 2602.08794\nAuthors: \nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We develop MOVA, a synchronized video-audio generation model with an asymmetric dual-tower architecture that leverages pre-trained video and audio generation models.\n  2. We design a fine-grained audio-video captioning pipeline to produce high-quality bimodal training data at scale.\n  3. By scaling video-audio training, we achieve continuous improvements in synchronization performance across both modalities.\n\nTags: related-work, we develop, we design, by scaling","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
